  "texts": [
    "By manipulating the KL divergence with different hyperparameter v, PCA induces two types of collapse: PCA+ (Objective 1) maximizes KL to create diffusion collapse, pushing the distribution out-of-distribution with |µ| → ∞ and σ 2 → ∞, thereby preserving original image content; PCA-(Objective 2) minimizes KL to create concentration collapse, collapsing the distribution to a Dirac δ function with µ → 0 and σ 2 → 0, thereby destroying semantic information.",
